---
const date = '2026-05-19';
const title = 'Legal-clarity cleanup: replaced verification overstatement with the 3-layer trust model across the marketing site';
---
<section class="space-y-2">
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">{date}</p>
  <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">{title}</h2>
  <p>
    Aligned <code>breederhq-www</code> with the legal-clarity remediation completed in the platform (see
    <code>docs/codebase/architecture/LEGAL-CLARITY-REMEDIATION-2026-06.md</code> and the help article
    <code>docs/help/articles/marketplace/trust-and-verification.md</code>). The marketplace no longer
    operates badges or tiers that imply BreederHQ verifies, vets, vouches for, or reviews providers,
    so the marketing site can no longer say it does.
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1.5">
    <li>
      <strong><code>/trust</code> rewritten from scratch.</strong> Hero, tier section, credential-verification
      examples, and reviews section all replaced with the three-layer model: Stripe Identity passthrough,
      public-registry passthrough (OFA / AKC / AFA / state licensing boards), and provider self-attestation.
      Profile Indicators (joined date, typical response time, completed transactions, open disputes)
      documented as account-history facts, not endorsements. Page title changed from
      "Trust &amp; Verification" to "Identity &amp; Credentials."
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Retired the "Verification Tiers + Earned Badges" sections</strong> on <code>/for-providers</code>,
      <code>/for-breeders</code>, <code>/index</code>, <code>/buyers</code>, and <code>/buyers/why-breederhq-marketplace</code>.
      Each replaced with a three-layer Identity &amp; Credentials block linking to <code>/trust</code>.
      Sibling FAQs that described nonexistent tier systems (ID Verified / Verified / Accredited) were
      rewritten to honestly describe what BreederHQ does and does not do.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Per-category sweep across <code>/for-providers/*</code>.</strong> Every "Optional verification badge for credentials"
      bullet, every "Upload your credentials for a verified badge" paragraph, and the Farriers page&rsquo;s
      "Verification Badges That Mean Something" section were replaced with three-layer language
      (Stripe Identity confirmation, AFA / registry passthrough where supported, provider attestation
      for everything else).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Buyer-facing &ldquo;Verified Breeders&rdquo; marketing copy neutralized.</strong> Removed claims
      about "verified breeders," "verified marketplace profile," "verified listings," "Browse Verified Breeders,"
      "Find verified breeders" headlines, and "Verification badges are earned through documented behavior"
      from species pages (cats, dogs, horses, goats, sheep, rabbits, alpacas, llamas, cattle), articles,
      <code>/about</code>, <code>/faq</code>, <code>/find-breeders/*</code>, <code>/compare/*</code>,
      <code>/workflows/*</code>, and <code>/buyers/health-guarantees</code>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Geographic and category pages.</strong> <code>/services/farriers</code>,
      <code>/services/farriers/kentucky</code>, <code>/services/equine-boarding</code>,
      <code>/services/equine-boarding/lexington-ky</code>, <code>/services/equine-boarding/ocala-fl</code>,
      and the Florida / Texas farrier geo pages now describe identity-and-credential indicators in
      passthrough terms only, with JSON-LD <code>offerDescription</code> rewritten to match.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Header, footer, and sibling-link labels.</strong> Renamed "Trust &amp; Verification" to
      "Identity &amp; Credentials" in <code>HeaderV2.astro</code> (desktop and mobile entries), the global
      <code>Footer.astro</code>, the <code>/for-providers/farriers</code> sibling block, and
      <code>/services/equine-boarding</code>&rsquo;s lower related-links list. URLs unchanged
      (<code>/trust</code> remains the canonical path).
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Operating principle reaffirmed: identity and credential display on BreederHQ is a passthrough plus
    self-attestation system, not a vouching system. The marketing site must match.
  </p>
</section>
